Governor Ifeanyi Okowa of Delta State on Monday congratulated Governor Godwin Nogheghase Obaseki of Edo State on his 60th birthday anniversary on July 1, 2019.
Okowa commended Obaseki’s ingenuity in working tirelessly to industrialise Edo State and making life easy for the people; acknowledging the Edo State Governor for his patriotic and unrelenting service to his state and the nation.
okowa in a statement in Asaba, observed that Governor Obaseki has provided purposeful, courageous and tenacious leadership for the people of Edo State in the last three years in the saddle.
“Your creativity in attracting resources to your state reflects absolutely in your competence and ability to develop the economy of Edo State.
“On the occasion of your 60th birthday anniversary today Monday 1st July, 2019, I write to heartily rejoice with you, your family and political associates on behalf of the Government and people of Delta State.
“In the past 60 years of a life of outstanding accomplishment and great personal fulfillment, you are currently serving your state with an uncommon sense of patriotism and unwavering dedication.
“On the auspicious occasion of your 60th birthday anniversary, I join your family, friends, political associates and well-wishers to thank Almighty God for your life which has been marked by outstanding accomplishments and enduring fulfillment,” Okowa declared.
Okowa prayed that God would grant Gov. Obaseki longer life, good health and wisdom in serving the people of Edo State and Nigeria in general.

			
